HEADWORD: Transmission dynamometer
<hw>Trans*mis"sion dy`na*mom"e*ter</hw>. <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A
dynamometer in which power is measured, without being absorbed or used
up, during transmission.</def>⟦br⟧
